text: Fenggui Cave () is a cave in Magong City, Penghu County, Taiwan. ==Name== The name Fenggui means a kind of wind cabinet of Chinese organ. ==History== The cave was formed by the continuous sea waves erosion on to its coastal areas. ==Architecture== The wave features a two-story shell-shaped pavilion nearby. ==See also== * Geology of Taiwan ==References== Category:Caves of Taiwan Category:Landforms of Penghu County
title: Fenggui Cave
